author: Ese Erheriene
title: Persistent China Demand Worries Push Copper Lower
text:
LONDON—Copper futures were lower in London on Friday, on the back of persistent worries about future demand from top consumer China.
The London Metal Exchange’s three-month copper contract was down 0.8% at $5,268 a metric ton in afternoon European trade.
